`` Hansel and Gretel '' -LRB- also known as Hansel and Grettel , Hansel and Grethel , or Little Brother and Little Sister -RRB- -LRB- -LSB- ˈhænsəl -RSB- or -LSB- ˈhɑːnsəl -RSB- and -LSB- ˈɡrɛtəl -RSB- Hänsel und Gretel -LSB- ˈhɛnzl̩ ʊnt ˈɡʁeːtl̩ -RSB- -RRB- is a well-known fairy tale of German origin , recorded by the Brothers Grimm and published in 1812 .
Hansel and Gretel are a young brother and sister kidnapped by a cannibalistic witch living deep in the forest in a house constructed of cake and confectionery .
The two children escape with their lives by outwitting her .
The tale has been adapted to various media , most notably the opera Hänsel und Gretel -LRB- 1893 -RRB- by Engelbert Humperdinck .
Under the Aarne -- Thompson classification system , `` Hansel and Gretel '' is classified under Class 327 .